properties.name: headers
cs_specversion
properties.description: The version of the schema, correlated to specversion.

properties.name: ce_id
properties.description: An identifier specific to this event.  ce_source+ce_id must be unique.  Correlates to id.

properties.name: ce_source
properties.description: URI-reference.  Identifies the context or application/service where the event occurred.  Correlates to source.

properties.name: ce_type
properties.description: Describes the type of event related to the originating occurrence.  Correlates to type.

properties.name: ce_time
properties.description: Represents when the event occurred.  RFC 3339 compliance timestamp with UTC offset.

properties.name: content-type
properties.description: Usually "application/json", but values per RFC 2016 and its modifications.  Correlates to datacontenttype.

properties.name: correlation_id
properties.description: An identifier assigned by the ce_source or ingestion point which should persist through the entire downstream cascade so we can tie them all together.

properties.name: x_CRMId
properties.description: Identifier assigned by the originating CRM system.
Elements which begin with "ce_" are inherited from cloudevents.io.

properties.name: x_OriginatingCompany

properties.name: agencyCase

properties.name: executionDate

properties.name: x_loanVersionNumber

properties.name: emailAddress
emailAddress
properties.description: The email address for the contact, as provided.

properties.name: x_standardizedEmail
properties.description: Future use.  The email address after applying data quality rules.  For example, a Gmail address may have the dots and "plus tag" removed.  This address is best used for matching and list management.

properties.name: x_mxDomain
properties.description: Future use.  The domain of the email service as determined by an MX lookup.  For example, a company using a vanity domain with Google's services would not indicate the capabilities of the email server, and hence which data quality rules we should use.

properties.name: x_optInToMarketing
properties.description: Future use.  Is this email address opted in to marketing emails?

properties.name: x_isDisposableDomain
properties.description: Future use.  Is this domain a disposable email domain?  This can play a part in scoring or fraud risks.
The email address for the contact.  URLA form field 1a.12

properties.name: employmentStatusType
properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the relative time frame of the employment (current or previous).  URLA form field 1b.1

properties.name: employerLegalName
properties.description: The unparsed name of either an individual or a legal entity.  URLA form field 1b.2

properties.name: employmentPositionDescription
properties.description: A free-form text field describing the borrower's employment position or title.  URLA form field 1b.5

properties.name: employmentStartDate
properties.description: The date that the borrower started the employment position with the employer.  URLA form field 1b.6

properties.name: employmentEndDate
properties.description: The date that the borrower ended the employment position with the employer.  This is not used for current employment.  URLA form field 1d.6

properties.description: The total number of complete months the borrower has been employed in the line of work or type of business. URLA form field 1b.7

properties.name: specialBorrowerEmployerRelationshipIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that the borrower is employed by a family member, property seller, real estate agent/broker, or other party to the transaction.  URLA form field 1b.8

properties.name: employmentBorrowerSelfEmployedIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that in the referenced employment the borrower is self-employed.  URLA form 1b.9

properties.name: ownershipInterestType
properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the percentage of the total business of the borrower's self-owned business.  URLA form 1b.9.1

properties.name: employmentMonthlyIncomeAmount
properties.description: The amount per month of income associated with the borrower's employment.  URLA form field 1b.9.2

properties.name: incomeItems
incomeType
properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies borrower income items on a mortgage loan application.

properties.name: currentIncomeMonthlyTotalAmount
properties.description: The monthly total amount for the specified Income Item.

properties.name: monthlyMilitaryEntitlementsAmount
properties.description: The total monthly amount of funds provided or credited to military personnel for specific needs, such as food or housing, over and above base pay.

The components of the total monthly income.  URLA form section 1b.10

Breaking from the design of the URLA/ULAD, employment income is indicated here.  Non-employment income is indicated in incomeOtherSources.

Section 1b of the URLA form, and 1d if there is a previous employment also (only if current is <2yrs).  When flattening these for Salesforce and events, there will need to be both a Current and a Previous.

properties.name: declarations
citizenshipResidencyType
properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the U.S. citizenship or alien status of the individual.  URLA form field 1a.5

properties.name: intentToOccupyType
properties.description: Borrower's answer to the question: Do you intend to occupy the property as your primary residence?  URLA form field 5a.1

properties.name: homeownerPastThreeYearsType
properties.description: Borrower's answer to the question: Have you had an ownership interest in a property in the last three years?.  URLA form field 5a.1.1

properties.name: priorPropertyUsageType
properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the actual usage of the borrower for the previously owned property.  URLA form field 5a.1.2

properties.name: FHASecondaryResidenceIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that the property usage falls under the FHA Secondary Residence policy and guidelines.  URLA form field 5a.1.2

properties.name: priorPropertyTitleType
properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies how the borrower held title to the property.  URLA form field 5a.1.3

properties.name: ULAD:SpecialBorrowerSellerRelationshipIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that the borrower has a family relationship or business affiliation with the seller of the property. URLA form field 5a.2

properties.name: undisclosedBorrowedFundsIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that some or all of the closing funds or down payment is borrowed or provided by another party, including the seller, and not disclosed on the mortgage loan application.  URLA form field 5a.3

properties.name: undisclosedBorrowedFundsAmount
properties.description: The amount of the closing funds or down payment that is borrowed or provided by another party, including the seller, and not disclosed on the mortgage loan application. URLA form field 5a.3.1

properties.name: undisclosedMortgageApplicationIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the borrower will apply for a mortgage loan on a property that is not the subject property on or before closing of this transaction that is not disclosed on this application.  URLA form field 5a.4.1

properties.name: undisclosedCreditApplicationIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the borrower will apply for other credit (not mortgage loan) prior to closing the mortgage transaction. URLA form field 5a.4.2

properties.name: propertyProposedCleanEnergyLienIndicator
properties.description:
When true, indicates that the property will be subject to a property clean energy lien that could take precedence over the first mortgage lien including PACE loan or other similar liens. URLA form field 5a.5

TODO: This may be better in the Subject Property section

properties.name: undisclosedComakerOfNoteIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that the Borrower is a co-signer or guarantor on other debts not disclosed on the loan application. URLA form field 5b.1

properties.name: outstandingJudgmentsIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the borrower has outstanding judgments against him or her. URLA form field 5b.2

properties.name: presentlyDelinquentIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the borrower is presently delinquent or in default on Federal debt or other loan mortgage, financial obligation, bond or loan guarantee. URLA form field 5b.3

properties.name: partyToLawsuitIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the borrower is a party to a lawsuit.  URLA form field 5b.4

properties.name: priorPropertyDeedInLieuConveyedIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the Borrower has conveyed property as deed in lieu of foreclosure within the past seven years. URLA form field 5b.5

properties.name: priorPropertyShortSaleCompletedIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the Borrower has completed a short sale or pre-foreclosure sale where the Lender accepted less than full value for the outstanding mortgage balance within the past seven years. URLA form field 5b.6

properties.name: priorPropertyForeclosureCompletedIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates the borrower has had property foreclosed upon within the past seven years. URLA form field 5b.7

properties.name: bankruptcyIndicator

Chapter under which bankruptcy has been filed. URLA form field 5b.8.1

In a break from the design of the URLA/ULAD, this is non-employment income only.  Employment income should be indicated with the employer.

properties.name: monthlyMilitaryEntitlementsAmount
properties.description: The total monthly amount of funds provided or credited to military personnel for specific needs, such as food or housing, over and above base pay. URLA form field 1b.10.5

properties.name: militaryService
selfDeclaredMilitaryServiceIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that the individual is self-reporting as having served, or is currently serving in the US Armed Forces. Includes enlisted persons that may not have served in Active Duty status, and service in the National Guard or Reserves. Also includes surviving spouses of Veterans who served and were Missing In Action (MIA) /Killed In Action (KIA), who died of a condition or impairment connected to their service in the Armed Forces (as determined by VA or DoD), or who self-report that their spouses service and connected disability/impairment entitles them to benefits from the VA.

properties.name: militaryStatusType
properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies duty status of current or former military personnel.

properties.name: spousalVABenefitsEligibilityIndicator
properties.description: When true, indicates that the individual is a surviving spouse of a Veteran who served and was Missing In Action (MIA) /Killed In Action (KIA), a Veteran who died of a condition or impairment connected to his/her service in the Armed Forces (as determined by VA or DoD), or a Veteran whose service connected disability/impairment, they believe, entitles them to benefits from the VA.

properties.name: constructionMethodType
properties.description:
Describes the construction process for the main dwelling unit of the subject property. URLA form field 4a.8

Despite being a yes/no question on the URLA, the value used in the ULAD is either "Manufactured" or (null).  The question asked on the form is "Is the property a manufactured home? (e.g., a factory built dwelling built on a permanent chassis)".

Use the LoanRoleType = RelatedLoan to describe a loan linked to the subject loan and collaterized by the same property. 
Use the LoanRoleType = SubjectLoan to describe the loan that is the object of the transaction, upon which the receiving business partner will take some action.

properties.description: The type of phone service as determined by a verification platform.  Usually "cellular" or "landline". properties.description: The telephone number for the contact.  Unformatted for now.
